'standard procedure', right?

883
00:38:48,550 --> 00:38:48,940
It is.

884
00:38:49,920 --> 00:38:50,260
Fine,

885
00:38:50,960 --> 00:38:51,490
let's see the paperwork.

886
00:38:52,440 --> 00:38:52,940
Show me.

887
00:38:54,630 --> 00:38:55,260
Any official notice?

888
00:38:56,280 --> 00:38:56,740
Got anything?

889
00:38:58,030 --> 00:38:58,740
Not at the moment.

890
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:00,980
In that case,

891
00:39:04,840 --> 00:39:05,610
please leave.

892
00:39:08,000 --> 00:39:09,650
You're not welcome here.

893
00:39:10,030 --> 00:39:10,690
Out!

894
00:39:14,800 --> 00:39:16,780
Take your device and leave!

895
00:39:16,960 --> 00:39:17,380
Get out!

896
00:39:18,880 --> 00:39:20,340
Doubting Xie like this...

897
00:39:21,440 --> 00:39:22,340
Ridiculous!

898
00:39:23,520 --> 00:39:31,800
[Prosecutor]

899
00:39:31,800 --> 00:39:32,650
Yes?

900
00:39:33,590 --> 00:39:35,860
Hong Liang came by

901
00:39:36,230 --> 00:39:37,420
with another guy!

902
00:39:38,320 --> 00:39:39,260
They were grilling me with questions!

903
00:39:40,030 --> 00:39:41,130
What's going on?

904
00:39:42,710 --> 00:39:44,300
Are you keeping something from me?

905
00:39:45,320 --> 00:39:46,530
You better get home, quick.

906
00:40:37,760 --> 00:40:38,860
We got nothing out of her.

907
00:40:40,150 --> 00:40:40,650
Mr. Hong,

908
00:40:41,230 --> 00:40:42,860
if she calls,

909
00:40:43,480 --> 00:40:44,010
what should I do?

910
00:40:44,920 --> 00:40:45,530
If she calls,

911
00:40:46,840 --> 00:40:47,940
pick up.

912
00:40:48,400 --> 00:40:49,050
Me?

913
00:40:49,510 --> 00:40:50,860
What am I even supposed to say?

914
00:40:51,190 --> 00:40:53,010
You're young,
you need this kind of experience.

915
00:40:54,190 --> 00:40:55,130
In our line of work,

916
00:40:55,230 --> 00:40:56,490
you can't be afraid to upset people.

917
00:40:58,710 --> 00:40:59,300
Well, Mr. Hong,

918
00:40:59,760 --> 00:41:00,340
let me ask you,

919
00:41:00,670 --> 00:41:02,090
if she called and you picked up,

920
00:41:02,280 --> 00:41:02,980
what would you say?

921
00:41:03,110 --> 00:41:04,090
I wouldn't pick up.

922
00:41:04,880 --> 00:41:05,900
I can't afford to cross that woman.

923
00:41:14,000 --> 00:41:14,780
Hello, Mr. Hong.

924
00:41:15,030 --> 00:41:16,860
Looks like Xie Hongfei's
on his way back to his hometown.

925
00:41:17,320 --> 00:41:18,900
Stay on him. We're on our way.

926
00:42:12,590 --> 00:42:13,340
Check if he's inside.

927
00:42:34,230 --> 00:42:34,570
Xie...

928
00:42:36,760 --> 00:42:37,490
Probably not this place.

929
00:42:41,630 --> 00:42:42,980
That's his scooter, Mr. Hong.

930
00:42:47,800 --> 00:42:48,460
Is that his?

931
00:42:48,960 --> 00:42:49,490
Should be.

932
00:42:57,880 --> 00:42:58,570
Go ahead.

933
00:43:15,760 --> 00:43:16,490
Anyone home?

934
00:43:17,190 --> 00:43:18,380
Coming.

935
00:43:25,840 --> 00:43:26,610
Hello, ma'am.

936
00:43:26,710 --> 00:43:27,650
Who are you?

937
00:43:28,550 --> 00:43:30,820
Is this Mr. Xie Hongfei's house?

938
00:43:31,480 --> 00:43:33,570
We're his colleagues,

939
00:43:34,030 --> 00:43:35,130
just need to ask a couple questions.

940
00:43:35,800 --> 00:43:36,860
He's at work.

941
00:43:37,360 --> 00:43:38,610
Why show up here?

942
00:43:59,760 --> 00:44:03,760
♪At the river's end,
bitter rain and brutal waves♪

943
00:44:03,760 --> 00:44:07,400
♪A human life is strewn with hardship♪

944
00:44:07,400 --> 00:44:11,200
♪Brother, there's a weight on my heart♪

945
00:44:11,200 --> 00:44:15,080
♪Until I meet Old Lady Meng,
I can't let it go♪

946
00:44:15,080 --> 00:44:18,800
♪Since ancient days,
black and white have stood apart♪

947
00:44:18,800 --> 00:44:22,440
♪Don't preach
that letting go makes you a Buddha♪

948
00:44:22,440 --> 00:44:26,080
♪Even good folk may die unrewarded♪

949
00:44:26,080 --> 00:44:30,720
♪So why should the wicked live in ease?♪

950
00:44:30,720 --> 00:44:38,080
♪For one last breath,
for one clear principle♪

951
00:44:38,080 --> 00:44:45,760
♪For this single rite,
I'll see it through to the end♪

952
00:44:45,760 --> 00:44:53,880
♪I will wear my life thin
just to glimpse the snow-orchid bloom♪

953
00:44:53,880 --> 00:45:01,280
♪I will shred these shoes
and barefoot tame the wind-blown sands♪

954
00:45:01,280 --> 00:45:08,880
♪I will face rosy clouds by day
and lift a torch by night♪

955
00:45:08,880 --> 00:45:15,960
♪Beneath the bright firmament,
I want every deed bound by law♪

956
00:45:15,960 --> 00:45:23,720
♪I want the ones who set out
to return home, no matter how late♪

957
00:45:23,720 --> 00:45:31,360
♪I want the rain that falls from heaven
to rise back into heaven♪

958
00:45:31,360 --> 00:45:38,560
♪I want to earn my daily bread
while guarding this wild land♪

959
00:45:38,560 --> 00:45:45,960
♪I want every righteous path on earth
to stand beneath clear skies♪

960
00:45:45,960 --> 00:45:53,720
♪I want the well-diggers' pockets
lined with salt♪

961
00:45:53,720 --> 00:46:01,600
♪And I want the heartless cheats
to feel the justice in their eyes♪
